1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,140
Echoes of the Unseen.

2
00:00:03,140 --> 00:00:05,639
Illyra traced the peeling wallpaper,

3
00:00:05,639 --> 00:00:11,179
the faded floral pattern barely discernible beneath layers of grime and neglect.

4
00:00:11,179 --> 00:00:17,019
The heir in Thorn Manor, her newly inherited ancestral home, hung thick and heavy,

5
00:00:17,019 --> 00:00:23,160
a suffocating tapestry woven from dust, damp, and the faint, sweet scent of decay.

6
00:00:23,160 --> 00:00:28,859
She'd never known her great-aunt Mildred, nor the crumbling edifice Mildred had bequeathed her,

7
00:00:28,899 --> 00:00:33,899
but the inheritance, however dilapidated, was a lifeline.

8
00:00:33,899 --> 00:00:37,600
Rent was due, her historians stipend laughably small,

9
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:41,399
and the student loans were a ravenous beast at her heels.

10
00:00:41,399 --> 00:00:46,379
The attic, a forgotten cavern of forgotten things, was where she'd started.

11
00:00:46,379 --> 00:00:53,719
The roof leaked less up here, and the light, filtered through a grimy skylight, was almost tolerable.

12
00:00:53,719 --> 00:00:58,420
Most of the boxes held brittle yellowed newspapers or moth-eaten textiles,

13
00:00:58,480 --> 00:01:04,079
but then, tucked away in a shadowed corner beneath a cobweb tarpaulin, she saw it.

14
00:01:04,079 --> 00:01:09,099
It was a box, no bigger than a shoebox, yet it commanded attention.

15
00:01:09,099 --> 00:01:15,400
Crafted from dark, polished wood, its surface was a labyrinth of intricate carvings, swirling knots,

16
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:23,240
abstract symbols that seemed to shift and writhe, and something that looked unsettlingly like a snarling maw.

17
00:01:23,299 --> 00:01:28,839
As her fingers brushed its cool surface, a faint hum resonated beneath her palm,

18
00:01:28,839 --> 00:01:33,879
a deep, unsettling thrum that seemed to vibrate in her very bones.

19
00:01:33,879 --> 00:01:40,179
It wasn't loud, more like a vibration felt than heard, like the distant tremor of a forgotten engine.

20
00:01:40,179 --> 00:01:44,079
Curiosity, a historian's fatal flaw, compelled her.

21
00:01:44,079 --> 00:01:49,319
There was no lock, just a delicate, almost invisible clasp.

22
00:01:49,339 --> 00:01:53,779
With a click that echoed too loudly in the silence, she unlatched it.

23
00:01:53,779 --> 00:01:56,219
The lid swung open with a sigh.

24
00:01:56,219 --> 00:01:59,819
There was no blinding light, no dramatic puff of smoke,

25
00:01:59,819 --> 00:02:07,560
only a deeper chill that plummeted the temperature of the already cool attic by several degrees, and then a shadow.

26
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:17,159
It wasn't a solid, defined form but a ripple in the air, a density that absorbed the scant light, stretching and contracting like a breath.

27
00:02:17,180 --> 00:02:24,120
It flowed out of the box, not rising but spreading, a formless ink blot expanding in the periphery of her vision.

28
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:27,120
Before Alera could even gasp, it was on her.

29
00:02:27,120 --> 00:02:29,659
Not on her exactly, but in her.

30
00:02:29,659 --> 00:02:36,699
A cold, piercing dread plunged into her chest, an internal darkness that seemed to bloom outward from her core.

31
00:02:36,699 --> 00:02:42,939
She stumbled back, hitting a stack of old trunks, the breath knocked from her lungs.

32
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:51,000
There was no physical contact, no sensation of being touched, yet she felt utterly invaded, her very essence seized.

33
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:54,000
The first few days she tried to rationalize it.

34
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:58,079
The flickering lights, the strange cold spots that appeared out of nowhere,

35
00:02:58,079 --> 00:03:05,280
the faint, disembodied whispers she heard at the edge of sleep drafts, old wiring, stress.

36
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:11,719
But then the whispers intensified, wrapping around her thoughts, insistent and chillingly clear.

37
00:03:11,719 --> 00:03:13,199
Welcome home.

38
00:03:13,199 --> 00:03:16,939
Her vitality once a robust river dwindled to a trickle.

39
00:03:16,939 --> 00:03:21,240
She felt constantly tired as if she'd run a marathon in her sleep.

40
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:24,680
Her skin was pallid, her eyes perpetually shadowed.

41
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:32,659
Food tasted like ash and the vibrant world around her seemed to dim, its colors muted, its sounds muffled.

42
00:03:32,659 --> 00:03:35,360
The phenomena escalated too.

43
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:39,819
Doors would creak open on their own, objects would subtly shift position,

44
00:03:39,859 --> 00:03:43,739
and once a teacup lifted from its saucer and crashed to the floor,

45
00:03:43,739 --> 00:03:48,039
shattering into a thousand pieces while Alera watched, frozen.

46
00:03:48,039 --> 00:03:52,280
The presence, she now understood, was no mere residual haunting.

47
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:55,280
It was active, deliberate.

48
00:03:55,280 --> 00:04:00,740
It began to communicate through vivid, terrifying visions that flashed behind her eyes,

49
00:04:00,740 --> 00:04:09,019
glimpses of ancient rites, of shadows dancing in flickering firelight, of a gaping void that promised oblivion.

50
00:04:09,020 --> 00:04:14,060
And through these visions and the relentless whispers that were no longer at the edge of her hearing,

51
00:04:14,060 --> 00:04:18,600
but inside her skull, it began to explain its demands.

52
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:22,579
It wasn't a choice of banishment, not exactly.

53
00:04:22,579 --> 00:04:25,879
It was a choice of containment or cohabitation.

54
00:04:25,879 --> 00:04:29,900
Seal me away, the whispers slithered into her thoughts one night,

55
00:04:29,900 --> 00:04:34,340
making her shiver despite the suffocating humidity of her bedroom.

56
00:04:34,339 --> 00:04:41,659
And you will pay, a piece of yourself sacrificed, a part of your soul severed forever quiet.

57
00:04:41,659 --> 00:04:47,500
The vision that followed was a searing pain, a phantom limb of her own spirit being torn away,

58
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:50,819
leaving behind a cold, echoing emptiness.

59
00:04:50,819 --> 00:04:53,779
The price was immense, terrifyingly intimate.

60
00:04:53,779 --> 00:04:55,759
Then came the alternative.

61
00:04:55,759 --> 00:04:59,159
Or embrace, embrace my power, become more.

62
00:04:59,159 --> 00:05:01,679
This promise was seductive, dangerous.

63
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:06,000
It showed her glimpses of impossible knowledge, of untold strength,

64
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:11,079
of a world seen through a lens of raw, untamed magic.

65
00:05:11,079 --> 00:05:14,800
But the visions accompanying this path were equally horrifying.

66
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:19,879
Her own face, contorted by madness, her sanity fraying like an old rope,

67
00:05:19,879 --> 00:05:25,079
the city outside dissolving into chaos, screams rising from unseen mouths

68
00:05:25,079 --> 00:05:30,840
as reality itself buckled under the strain of unleashed, unfettered power.

69
00:05:30,859 --> 00:05:35,099
Risk your mind, risk your world for true dominion.

70
00:05:35,099 --> 00:05:40,939
Alera pressed her hands to her temples, trying to shut out the relentless assault.

71
00:05:40,939 --> 00:05:46,979
It had latched onto her, feeding, growing, demanding a terrible, impossible decision.

72
00:05:46,979 --> 00:05:52,139
Seal it away and lose a part of herself, become a hollowed out shell, albeit safe.

73
00:05:52,139 --> 00:05:56,259
Or embrace its power, transcend her humanity, and risk becoming a monster

74
00:05:56,259 --> 00:05:59,819
that would unleash untold horror upon the world.

75
00:05:59,819 --> 00:06:04,620
The whispers swelled, a crescendo of ancient voices, indistinguishable yet

76
00:06:04,620 --> 00:06:08,240
terrifyingly clear, pressing in on her from all sides.

77
00:06:09,740 --> 00:06:14,639
The room spun, the walls seemed to breathe, distorting into grotesque shapes.

78
00:06:14,639 --> 00:06:17,039
Her breath hitched, her lungs burning,

79
00:06:17,039 --> 00:06:21,920
the draining feeling intensified, a cold suction at the very core of her being.

80
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:25,740
She staggered, her legs giving out, and she collapsed to the floor,

81
00:06:25,740 --> 00:06:28,860
hitting the worn rug with a dull thud.

82
00:06:28,860 --> 00:06:33,980
As darkness swallowed her, a searing, white hot pain blossomed on her left forearm.

83
00:06:35,460 --> 00:06:39,580
It felt like a brand, a cauterizing iron against her skin.

84
00:06:39,580 --> 00:06:44,540
She gasped, arching her back even as unconsciousness claimed her.

85
00:06:44,540 --> 00:06:48,660
The last thing she saw, superimposed over the blackness, was a stark,

86
00:06:48,660 --> 00:06:51,780
intricate symbol, burning itself into her flesh,

87
00:06:51,780 --> 00:06:55,139
its cryptic lines glowing with an unholy light.

88
00:06:55,139 --> 00:06:58,180
It was no longer just a haunting, it was a claiming.

89
00:06:59,379 --> 00:07:03,500
Illera awoke to the acrid tang of dust and ozone.

90
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:08,740
Her head throbbed, a dull drumbeat echoing the frantic pulse in her ears.

91
00:07:08,740 --> 00:07:13,220
The floorboards, ancient and unforgiving, dug into her cheek, and

92
00:07:13,220 --> 00:07:16,220
the air in the attic was thick with a palpable dread.

93
00:07:17,780 --> 00:07:21,819
Her hand instinctively went to her wrist, where the cryptic symbol,

94
00:07:21,819 --> 00:07:26,100
burnt crimson into her skin, pulsed with a feverish heat.

95
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:29,700
It wasn't just a mark, it was a throbbing, physical presence,

96
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:34,060
a constant reminder of the unseen thing that had latched onto her.

97
00:07:34,060 --> 00:07:36,900
Desperation was a cold, sharp blade.

98
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:37,580
She needed help.

99
00:07:39,180 --> 00:07:43,100
Not the kind her general practitioner could offer, nor a therapist.

100
00:07:43,100 --> 00:07:45,220
This was beyond their purview.

101
00:07:45,220 --> 00:07:49,140
Her mind, despite its haze of fear, fixated on one name,

102
00:07:49,140 --> 00:07:53,939
Professor Eris Thorne, reclusive, eccentric.

103
00:07:53,939 --> 00:07:58,139
Rumors from her university days painted him as a man obsessed with forgotten

104
00:07:58,139 --> 00:07:59,699
histories with the arcane.

105
00:08:01,219 --> 00:08:03,740
He was her last, impossible hope.

106
00:08:03,740 --> 00:08:06,300
The call was brief, stilted.

107
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:08,620
Eris Thorne's voice, raspy and

108
00:08:08,620 --> 00:08:13,620
edged with an academic's impatience, sounded precisely as she remembered.

109
00:08:13,620 --> 00:08:19,100
Miss Vance, I recall your dissertation on Neo-Victorian architectural influences.

110
00:08:20,579 --> 00:08:23,339
Why are you calling me about disturbances?

111
00:08:23,339 --> 00:08:27,579
He had clearly dismissed her initial stammering attempts to explain.

112
00:08:27,579 --> 00:08:31,139
Professor, please, Elera pleaded, her voice cracking.

113
00:08:31,139 --> 00:08:34,500
It's real, it's here in my home, it's draining me, and

114
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:36,379
I don't know what it wants.

115
00:08:36,379 --> 00:08:39,860
She left out the symbol, the chilling whispers, the terrible choice.

116
00:08:41,379 --> 00:08:42,899
He wouldn't believe her yet.

117
00:08:42,899 --> 00:08:45,539
His sigh was a gust of dry leaves.

118
00:08:45,539 --> 00:08:49,899
Very well, a quick consultation, my office, tomorrow at ten, and

119
00:08:49,899 --> 00:08:51,500
bring your strongest coffee.

120
00:08:52,460 --> 00:08:54,340
Elera barely slept.

121
00:08:54,340 --> 00:08:58,019
Every creek of the house, every shadow thrown by the streetlights,

122
00:08:58,019 --> 00:08:58,980
became a monster.

123
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:05,179
The whispers, no longer faint, hissed just at the edge of her hearing,

124
00:09:05,179 --> 00:09:08,460
a chorus of forgotten languages that scraped at her sanity.

125
00:09:09,580 --> 00:09:12,700
She arrived at Eris's office looking like a wraith,

126
00:09:12,700 --> 00:09:16,139
the symbol on her wrist visible despite her long sleeve.

127
00:09:16,299 --> 00:09:19,299
Eris Thorne was a man of sharp angles and

128
00:09:19,299 --> 00:09:25,100
even sharper eyes, framed by a wild mane of gray hair.

129
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:30,340
He watched her across a desk, cluttered with dusty tomes and forgotten artifacts.

130
00:09:30,340 --> 00:09:35,019
He listened, interjecting only with dry questions about her mental state,

131
00:09:35,019 --> 00:09:36,740
her sleep patterns, her diet.

132
00:09:38,379 --> 00:09:40,139
He was unimpressed, skeptical.

133
00:09:41,139 --> 00:09:44,779
Miss Vance, what you describe are classic symptoms of stress,

134
00:09:44,779 --> 00:09:48,539
exhaustion, perhaps even hypnagogic hallucinations.

135
00:09:48,539 --> 00:09:52,980
He began, tapping a pen against a heavy leather bound book.

136
00:09:52,980 --> 00:09:55,620
Just as he spoke, a tremor ran through the room.

137
00:09:57,100 --> 00:10:01,620
A small ornate inquel on his desk tipped over with a soft clatter,

138
00:10:01,620 --> 00:10:04,779
spreading a dark stain across an antique map.

139
00:10:04,779 --> 00:10:07,659
Eris stiffened, his eyes narrowing.

140
00:10:07,659 --> 00:10:12,179
Elera felt a chill, a familiar draining sensation as the entity made its

141
00:10:12,179 --> 00:10:13,740
presence known.

142
00:10:13,740 --> 00:10:16,659
The temperature in the room dropped several degrees,

143
00:10:16,659 --> 00:10:18,620
the air growing heavy, oppressive.

144
00:10:20,259 --> 00:10:23,379
Remarkable, Eris murmured, not quite a question.

145
00:10:23,379 --> 00:10:28,340
He picked up the inquel examining it, a draft perhaps.

146
00:10:28,340 --> 00:10:32,460
But his gaze met Elera's, and for the first time she saw a flicker of something

147
00:10:32,460 --> 00:10:38,419
beyond academic detachment, a spark of intrigue, a hint of unsettling recognition.

148
00:10:38,419 --> 00:10:45,899
Over the next few days, Eris became less skeptical, more intensely focused.

149
00:10:45,899 --> 00:10:51,339
He visited the ancestral home, feeling the undeniable oppressive atmosphere.

150
00:10:51,339 --> 00:10:55,259
He witnessed objects levitate briefly, heard the faint,

151
00:10:55,259 --> 00:10:58,860
unsettling hum that resonated deep in the house's bones.

152
00:11:00,339 --> 00:11:03,500
He saw the deepening shadows beneath Elera's eyes,

153
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:06,939
the way her frame seemed to shrink with each passing hour.

154
00:11:06,940 --> 00:11:10,580
And then he saw the symbol on her wrist, his expression,

155
00:11:10,580 --> 00:11:15,020
usually so guarded, shifted, revealing a profound disquiet.

156
00:11:15,020 --> 00:11:15,520
This.

157
00:11:16,940 --> 00:11:19,780
This is not merely a haunting, Elera, he said,

158
00:11:19,780 --> 00:11:21,780
tracing the symbol with a hesitant finger.

159
00:11:22,820 --> 00:11:27,820
This is a binding, a pact, and that hum, it's a lament or a hungry growl.

160
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:33,220
Together they delved into her family history, guided by the few scattered

161
00:11:33,259 --> 00:11:37,660
documents Elera had found in Eris's extensive, peculiar library.

162
00:11:39,139 --> 00:11:43,660
They unearthed diaries, brittle letters, and fragmented ledgers that spoke of

163
00:11:43,660 --> 00:11:47,540
hidden chambers, forbidden knowledge, and whispers of the protector.

164
00:11:48,580 --> 00:11:53,740
The Vance bloodline, it seemed, was steeped in more than just land and titles.

165
00:11:53,740 --> 00:11:57,899
There were veiled references to sight, to weaving the unseen, and

166
00:11:57,899 --> 00:12:01,300
to dark rituals performed to secure unearthly power.

167
00:12:01,299 --> 00:12:05,019
The family, far from being ordinary historians,

168
00:12:05,019 --> 00:12:09,659
had been something else entirely, occultists, summoners,

169
00:12:09,659 --> 00:12:13,899
perhaps even wardens of something ancient and terrible.

170
00:12:13,899 --> 00:12:18,379
Your ancestors were dabblers, Eris declared one evening,

171
00:12:18,379 --> 00:12:21,939
surrounded by scrolls and dusty manuscripts,

172
00:12:21,939 --> 00:12:24,979
the air thick with the scent of old paper.

173
00:12:24,979 --> 00:12:30,139
They sought to bind forces beyond their understanding to use them for protection,

174
00:12:30,340 --> 00:12:33,379
for prosperity, but there's always a price.

175
00:12:33,379 --> 00:12:38,580
Elera, growing weaker by the day, tried everything they found.

176
00:12:38,580 --> 00:12:42,340
She hung sachets of rue and rosemary above doorways,

177
00:12:42,340 --> 00:12:45,299
whispered protective psalms into the night,

178
00:12:45,299 --> 00:12:49,299
drew symbols of banishment with chalk on the floorboards.

179
00:12:49,299 --> 00:12:51,939
But each attempt backfired spectacularly.

180
00:12:51,939 --> 00:12:57,220
A simple protection charm woven from elder wood burst into splinters,

181
00:12:57,420 --> 00:13:02,820
a mirror reflecting her tired face shattered into a thousand jagged pieces.

182
00:13:02,820 --> 00:13:06,620
The humming intensified, the air grew colder, and

183
00:13:06,620 --> 00:13:11,820
the whispers became more distinct, twisting her name, mocking her efforts.

184
00:13:11,820 --> 00:13:17,980
The entity's manifestations escalated from subtle disturbances to outright aggression.

185
00:13:17,980 --> 00:13:21,580
A book flew from a shelf, narrowly missing her head.

186
00:13:21,580 --> 00:13:26,139
The kettle boiled over, scalding her hand as if pushed by a stone.

187
00:13:26,179 --> 00:13:29,659
Her hand as if pushed by an unseen force.

188
00:13:29,659 --> 00:13:33,340
She'd wake to find her hair tangled, her skin bearing faint,

189
00:13:33,340 --> 00:13:35,740
cold imprints of unseen fingers.

190
00:13:37,259 --> 00:13:40,179
Sleep was a luxury she could no longer afford.

191
00:13:40,179 --> 00:13:44,419
The nightmares were vivid, terrifying encounters with a shadowy figure that

192
00:13:44,419 --> 00:13:47,980
drained her strength, leaving her gasping for breath,

193
00:13:47,980 --> 00:13:50,980
the symbol on her wrist burning like a fresh wound.

194
00:13:52,100 --> 00:13:55,580
Liam, bless his oblivious heart, remained a constant.

195
00:13:57,100 --> 00:14:01,100
He'd helped Alera digitize some of the more fragile family documents,

196
00:14:01,100 --> 00:14:04,620
pouring over them with her in the dim light of the study.

197
00:14:04,620 --> 00:14:09,139
He'd bring her coffee, distract her with anecdotes about his own research into

198
00:14:09,139 --> 00:14:13,379
forgotten architecture, but even he began to change.

199
00:14:13,379 --> 00:14:18,580
Crazy dreams last night, Alera, he'd yawned one morning, rubbing his temples.

200
00:14:20,059 --> 00:14:25,419
Felt like I was running through tar, and I swear I heard your name being whispered.

201
00:14:25,419 --> 00:14:29,219
Alera brushed it off, too consumed by her own terror, but

202
00:14:29,219 --> 00:14:32,379
the dreams became a nightly occurrence for Liam.

203
00:14:32,379 --> 00:14:37,219
He grew pale, his usual energetic banter replaced by a quiet weariness.

204
00:14:38,699 --> 00:14:42,779
He'd complain of a persistent chill, even indoors.

205
00:14:42,779 --> 00:14:47,299
He'd stare into empty corners of the room as if seeing something Alera couldn't,

206
00:14:47,299 --> 00:14:50,299
a furrow in his brow that spoke of a growing unease.

207
00:14:51,259 --> 00:14:56,779
One evening, as Alera tried a particularly potent banishing right involving salt and

208
00:14:56,779 --> 00:14:58,779
iron, the house erupted.

209
00:15:00,259 --> 00:15:05,179
Glass exploded in the kitchen, a searing pain lanced through Alera's arm as

210
00:15:05,179 --> 00:15:08,299
a shard embedded itself in her flesh.

211
00:15:08,299 --> 00:15:14,299
The humming in the house rose to a deafening roar, a cacophony of agony and triumph.

212
00:15:14,299 --> 00:15:18,419
A gust of frigid air slammed her against the wall, stealing her breath.

213
00:15:18,419 --> 00:15:23,299
She crumpled, the world tilting precariously.

214
00:15:23,299 --> 00:15:27,219
She must have passed out, or perhaps just fallen into a desperate,

215
00:15:27,219 --> 00:15:29,379
short-lived slumber.

216
00:15:29,379 --> 00:15:31,620
When she came to, the house was silent, but

217
00:15:31,620 --> 00:15:35,579
a new profound chill permeated every molecule of air.

218
00:15:35,579 --> 00:15:38,379
Her arm throbbed, crusted with dried blood.

219
00:15:39,899 --> 00:15:43,579
She staggered to her feet, her legs weak, her head spinning.

220
00:15:43,579 --> 00:15:47,699
Her room was a wreck, not just disarray, but devastation.

221
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:50,980
Furniture was overturned, curtains ripped from their rods,

222
00:15:50,980 --> 00:15:54,220
books strewn across the floor, their pages torn.

223
00:15:54,220 --> 00:15:58,020
It looked as if a whirlwind had torn through it, panic clawed at her throat.

224
00:15:59,660 --> 00:16:03,300
She stumbled over something on the floor and looked down.

225
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:06,660
Carved deep into the ancient floorboards with a jagged,

226
00:16:06,660 --> 00:16:10,700
furious precision was a single, chilling message.

227
00:16:10,700 --> 00:16:14,740
It wasn't in any script she recognized, but the meaning was clear,

